Rating: 3
These were very good with just a couple of adjustments. The meat mixture made enough for at least eight large rolls, with a little left over. Seven rolls and I wouldn't have been able to close the sides of the rolls. I left out the white sugar as I was sure it would make the dish too sweet. The cooking liquid is very soupy at the end, but I'm not a fan of cornstarch, so I covered the cabbage rolls and kept them warm in the oven while I reduced the liquid for 30 minutes. Excellent!

