Rating: 3
All in all this was great, but we had to make some changes!! Luckily we only made half this recipe the 1st night, and the 2nd half the next night becuase the rice was completely uncooked the 1st time we made this!! Instead of simmering in a pot on the stovetop, we baked it the 2nd night in the oven in a covered casserole dish. Worked perfectly, and all the rice was cooked! If you want to simmer it, use cooked rice instead. Other modifications - used ground turkey meat instead of beef, zested fruit rinds instead of keeping whole chunks, cut sugar down to 1/4 (actually used purevia in its place), and cut water down to 1 cup. Not sure you need the white sugar at all, or use even less brown/white sugar. Was just a bit too sweet. We also used Splenda brown. Last thing - we also put the sauce in the blender the 2nd night instead of serving it with whole pieced of fruit in it - liked it a lot better! Lots of work, but this dish really was amazing with the slight tweaks. Great flavors!!!

